<p>I have a default state and 2 modal states.  When the modal is open and I go to another modal state the parent view is refreshing.  Is there a way to prevent this from happening?</p>  <pre><code>.state 'main',   url: '/main',   templateUrl: '/views/main.html',   controller: 'MainCtrl' .state 'main.company',   url: '/company',   onEnter: ($modal) -&gt;     $modal.open       templateUrl: '/views/company.html',       controller: 'CompanyCtrl',       animation: true,       size: 'sm'     return  .state 'main.form',    url: '/form',    onEnter: ($modal) -&gt;    $modal.open      templateUrl: '/views/form.html',      controller: 'FormCtrl',      animation: true,      size: 'sm'    return </code></pre>